race.comment: RIVERSDALE MICK (8) was in winning form two back (22.65) at Geelong but ran below best last time at Sandown, finishing 6th. Tough to beat if on-song. MARSHALL BEAR (1) made light work of the tricky draw with a scorching early sectional but gathered in and had to settle for the minors, finishing second (27.33) at Horsham over 485m. Leading chance. CRACKERJACK KEV (3) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing fifth (26.11) last time in a Grade 5 at Geelong. Form at the trip sound including two wins. Bold showing expected. SHOW CAUSE (7) boasts a solid strike-rate over this track and distance.
